cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.CC, cs.DM 

The paper deals with the calculation of the finite-state dimension of a set of infinite sequences over a finite alphabet, based on given conditions on the asymptotic frequencies of symbols in the sequences. This involves concepts from information theory (Shannon entropy) and fractal geometry (Hausdorff and packing dimensions). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also uses techniques from discrete mathematics (combinatorics, graph theory) and computational complexity theory (polynomial-time dimensions), making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses multifractal analysis, which falls under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
